title: Grateful Dead Live at Fox Theater on 1985-10-29
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1) -> Sound Devices 744T (24bit/96k) -> Samplitude Professional v10.22 -> FLAC/16
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger, Friend Of The Devil, Minglewood Blues, Bird Song, Hell In A Bucket-> Deal

Set 2

Mississippi Half Step-> Franklin's Tower-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Crazy Fingers-> Drums-> The Wheel-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Johnny B. Goode, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: Love it No one makes better quality tapes then this crew rite here. Probably due to be connected to the band even though others were connected this team has the experience. I thank you ever time I click on one of your copy's. I couldn't imagine how many other tapers must of wanted to dub your tapes each night.

Incredible Quality -- Tape and People The tape quality speaks for itself.  

The quality of the people who shared so many incredible quality tapes that so many of us enjoyed so much.  

All I can say is:  Thanks.  And I hope I get a chance to change your flat tire for you someday.

And maybe heal you too . . . . (That's a joke Doctor-- you take public service to a new level.)

Ahh, for a time machine I wasn't familiar with this show.  This is a great recording, great sound.   Maybe not full of all-time bests, but many strong performances.  I don't quibble with those that pick '69, '72-74 or 77 as the band's apex.  It is remarkable though to just dial in an 80s show of the so many they played, just grab it and find so many gems. Bet the folks in the house that night had a blast.  Thanks again to those who got this to my ears.
